Here is a CSS code that can be used to achieve a light red color with a medium light shade of pink:

.light-red-pink {
  background-color: #FFC0CB; /* Light red */
  filter: grayscale(10%); /* Add a medium light shade of pink */
}

Alternatively, you can use the following CSS code to achieve a similar effect:

.light-red-pink {
  background-color: #FF99CC; /* Light red */
  filter: hue-adjust(100%, 100%, 50%); /* Add a medium light shade of pink */
}

Both of these codes will give you a light red color with a medium light shade of pink. You can adjust the values of the filter property to achieve the desired shade of pink.
